U.S. Embassy Kigali, Rwanda
Yesterday at 8:30 AM ·

Today is the International Day of Commemoration and Dignity of the Victims of the Crime of Genocide and of the Prevention of this Crime. Our Ambassadors Fund fo...r Cultural Preservation grant of US$100,000 advances a partnership established in 2015 between Kwibuka Rwanda -- CNLG and PennDesign. This new funding will allow experts from the world-renown University of Pennsylvania to continue their work with Rwandan partners to develop first-of-its-kind conservation techniques for thousands of items of clothing recovered from the bodies of those who died at Nyamata church. This critical work will protect important heritage at Nyamata, will build skills and capacity to enable CNLG to preserve other memorial sites around Rwanda, and will provide an innovative blueprint for similar work around the world. The people of the United States stand with the people of Rwanda in memory of those who lost their lives in 1994. #kwibuka #AFCP

For more, visit http://bit.ly/2ASg7bj.
